  "prompt": "What should you do If you don\u2019t get accepted into the NLU through the CLAT?",
  "response": "If you don't get accepted into a National Law University (NLU) through the Common Law Admission Test (CLAT), here are several alternative options:\n\n1. Other Law Entrance Exams\n- AILET (All India Law Entrance Test)\n- LSAT India\n- MH CET Law\n- SLAT (Symbiosis Law Admission Test)\n\n2. Private Law Colleges\n- NALSAR\n- Symbiosis Law School\n- Christ University\n- Amity Law School\n- ILS Law College, Pune\n\n3. Alternative Career Paths\n- Pursue a regular LLB from a state university\n- Consider integrated law programs\n- Study humanities or social sciences\n- Explore legal process outsourcing\n- Pursue paralegal courses\n\n4. Skill Development\n- Improve CLAT preparation\n- Take coaching classes\n- Practice mock tests\n- Enhance legal knowledge\n- Develop communication skills\n\n5. Reappear for CLAT\n- Prepare more strategically\n- Analyze previous attempts\n- Focus on weak areas\n- Consider professional guidance\n\n6. International Options\n- Foreign law schools\n- International legal education programs\n\nRemember to stay motivated and explore multiple opportunities in the legal field.",
